In this folder we are to develop finished map generation pipelines. We have two basic types of modules: 1) generators and 2) adjustors. Generators create overlays and other metainformation about the map to serve as input for other generators and adjustors; these classes always return a struct with meta data, and often an overlay. Adjustors paint the actual main map, based on its own algorithm, the state of the map, and input made by generators. Generators will have been intended for a pipeline, and so have a prefix like "p1_gen"; adjustors will similarly have a prefix like "p1_adj". No class is allowed to use templates or STL. When an array is needed the class should instead checkout a whiteboard from the whiteboard manager. These memory blocks will be sized to 2 bytes times the number of tiles on the map. Any whiteboard block that is checked out should be placed in a thin wrapper; and this class should return its memory to the manager when the destructor is called. It is fine for a generator return-struct to have a whiteboard in it.

Test drivers should place images in a folder based in the current process and seed; e.g., p1-seed-42. For all generators and adjustors, the size is a variable.  
